      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While St. John's Wort may help with mood, it's not recommended to take it with sertraline. The combination can increase the risk of serotonin syndrome, a potentially life-threatening condition. St. John's Wort can also interact with sertraline, reducing its effectiveness and increasing the risk of side effects. It's best to consult your doctor or a pharmacist before adding any supplements to your routine, especially when taking prescription medication.",
